The paper deals with improving the performance of deep neural networks on image classification tasks through data augmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces an adversarial method for optimizing the augmentation policy, which involves training two networks to compete against each other, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as reinforcement learning and policy optimization, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
